    "content" : "Right I have loitered around in the background long enough, skimming off nuggets of common sense and hot tips from the forum. Thanks by the way!!!\n<br> So here goes,\n<br> I'm Justin, from Cornwall.\n<br> This is Barry, my 1964 bus, bought him (then named Minty) last year thinking I would have a bus to camp in with the wife and kids this summer . . . . . . . . Nope!\n<br> From what I gather he originally came from Sweden. And used to be bright yellow!\n<br> I knew it needed a bit of work but once you start these things, inevitably more work is found \n<img class=\"smilies\" src=\"./images/smilies/icon_eek.gif\" width=\"15\" height=\"15\" alt=\"8O\" title=\"eek\"> \n<br> As my welding can only be described at best as Agriculural, all the body work and welding is being done by Volksweld here in Cornwall\n<br> And here's the pics of so far, still a way to go . . . . . . .\n<br> So this is the last time I drove him, being dropped before all the work started!\n<br> \n<a href=\"http://s1127.photobucket.com/user/justinwesty/media/Barry/image.jpg1_zps5rbftzxh.jpg.html\" class=\"postlink\"><img src=\"http://i1127.photobucket.com/albums/l627/justinwesty/Barry/image.jpg1_zps5rbftzxh.jpg\" class=\"postimage\" alt=\"Image\"></a>\n<br> \n<a href=\"http://s1127.photobucket.com/user/justinwesty/media/Barry/image.jpg1_zpsidxvxan4.jpg.html\" class=\"postlink\"><img src=\"http://i1127.photobucket.com/albums/l627/justinwesty/Barry/image.jpg1_zpsidxvxan4.jpg\" class=\"postimage\" alt=\"Image\"></a>\n<br> First up, the roof .. . Previous owner had a roof rack with ornamental leather suitcases on all year round so not surprise there was a bit of rot up here\n<br> \n<a href=\"http://s1127.photobucket.com/user/justinwesty/media/Barry/image.jpg14_zpsrtddkza9.jpg.html\" class=\"postlink\"><img src=\"http://i1127.photobucket.com/albums/l627/justinwesty/Barry/image.jpg14_zpsrtddkza9.jpg\" class=\"postimage\" alt=\"Image\"></a>\n<br> \n<a href=\"http://s1127.photobucket.com/user/justinwesty/media/Barry/image.jpg15_zpsmdtj49ls.jpg.html\" class=\"postlink\"><img src=\"http://i1127.photobucket.com/albums/l627/justinwesty/Barry/image.jpg15_zpsmdtj49ls.jpg\" class=\"postimage\" alt=\"Image\"></a>\n<br> \n<a href=\"http://s1127.photobucket.com/user/justinwesty/media/Barry/image.jpg16_zpswcuqnwnd.jpg.html\" class=\"postlink\"><img src=\"http://i1127.photobucket.com/albums/l627/justinwesty/Barry/image.jpg16_zpswcuqnwnd.jpg\" class=\"postimage\" alt=\"Image\"></a>\n<br> \n<a href=\"http://s1127.photobucket.com/user/justinwesty/media/Barry/image.jpg18_zpswm76izid.jpg.html\" class=\"postlink\"><img src=\"http://i1127.photobucket.com/albums/l627/justinwesty/Barry/image.jpg18_zpswm76izid.jpg\" class=\"postimage\" alt=\"Image\"></a>\n<br> \n<a href=\"http://s1127.photobucket.com/user/justinwesty/media/Barry/image.jpg19_zpskh4wictp.jpg.html\" class=\"postlink\"><img src=\"http://i1127.photobucket.com/albums/l627/justinwesty/Barry/image.jpg19_zpskh4wictp.jpg\" class=\"postimage\" alt=\"Image\"></a>\n<br> And the rear quarter panel only had a small bit of rust, however this filler sculpture was discovered, guess all the water had got in behind the filler as it just fell off. . . \n<img class=\"smilies\" src=\"./images/smilies/icon_eek.gif\" width=\"15\" height=\"15\" alt=\"8O\" title=\"eek\"> \n<br> \n<a href=\"http://s1127.photobucket.com/user/justinwesty/media/Barry/image.jpg21_zpsw11iyazd.jpg.html\" class=\"postlink\"><img src=\"http://i1127.photobucket.com/albums/l627/justinwesty/Barry/image.jpg21_zpsw11iyazd.jpg\" class=\"postimage\" alt=\"Image\"></a>\n<br> \n<a href=\"http://s1127.photobucket.com/user/justinwesty/media/Barry/image.jpg22_zpsiem4goh1.jpg.html\" class=\"postlink\"><img src=\"http://i1127.photobucket.com/albums/l627/justinwesty/Barry/image.jpg22_zpsiem4goh1.jpg\" class=\"postimage\" alt=\"Image\"></a>\n<br> You can see the battery tray all bashed up, hence all the filler in the panel, must have taken quite a knock. photos don't show it but at its thickest the filler was just shy of an inch thick!\n<br> \n<a href=\"http://s1127.photobucket.com/user/justinwesty/media/Barry/image.jpg24_zpspddgwh8x.jpg.html\" class=\"postlink\"><img src=\"http://i1127.photobucket.com/albums/l627/justinwesty/Barry/image.jpg24_zpspddgwh8x.jpg\" class=\"postimage\" alt=\"Image\"></a>\n<br> \n<a href=\"http://s1127.photobucket.com/user/justinwesty/media/Barry/image.jpg25_zpsfip6jnxx.jpg.html\" class=\"postlink\"><img src=\"http://i1127.photobucket.com/albums/l627/justinwesty/Barry/image.jpg25_zpsfip6jnxx.jpg\" class=\"postimage\" alt=\"Image\"></a>\n<br> Cab step got a seeing to as well\n<br> \n<a href=\"http://s1127.photobucket.com/user/justinwesty/media/Barry/image.jpg32_zpszx8sx0n1.jpg.html\" class=\"postlink\"><img src=\"http://i1127.photobucket.com/albums/l627/justinwesty/Barry/image.jpg32_zpszx8sx0n1.jpg\" class=\"postimage\" alt=\"Image\"></a>\n<br> \n<a href=\"http://s1127.photobucket.com/user/justinwesty/media/Barry/image.jpg34_zpsnypkheue.jpg.html\" class=\"postlink\"><img src=\"http://i1127.photobucket.com/albums/l627/justinwesty/Barry/image.jpg34_zpsnypkheue.jpg\" class=\"postimage\" alt=\"Image\"></a>\n<br> \n<a href=\"http://s1127.photobucket.com/user/justinwesty/media/Barry/image.jpg35_zpswdc4fzae.jpg.html\" class=\"postlink\"><img src=\"http://i1127.photobucket.com/albums/l627/justinwesty/Barry/image.jpg35_zpswdc4fzae.jpg\" class=\"postimage\" alt=\"Image\"></a>\n<br> \n<a href=\"http://s1127.photobucket.com/user/justinwesty/media/Barry/image.jpg37_zpsqpyk9tdo.jpg.html\" class=\"postlink\"><img src=\"http://i1127.photobucket.com/albums/l627/justinwesty/Barry/image.jpg37_zpsqpyk9tdo.jpg\" class=\"postimage\" alt=\"Image\"></a>\n<br> Front lip got a bit of new metal also.\n<br> \n<a href=\"http://s1127.photobucket.com/user/justinwesty/media/Barry/image.jpg33_zps1cyhtiqv.jpg.html\" class=\"postlink\"><img src=\"http://i1127.photobucket.com/albums/l627/justinwesty/Barry/image.jpg33_zps1cyhtiqv.jpg\" class=\"postimage\" alt=\"Image\"></a>\n<br> \n<a href=\"http://s1127.photobucket.com/user/justinwesty/media/Barry/image.jpg36_zpsmlqawqho.jpg.html\" class=\"postlink\"><img src=\"http://i1127.photobucket.com/albums/l627/justinwesty/Barry/image.jpg36_zpsmlqawqho.jpg\" class=\"postimage\" alt=\"Image\"></a>\n<br> Little patch on outer sill on passenger side\n<br> \n<a href=\"http://s1127.photobucket.com/user/justinwesty/media/Barry/image.jpg27_zpsumvuvlus.jpg.html\" class=\"postlink\"><img src=\"http://i1127.photobucket.com/albums/l627/justinwesty/Barry/image.jpg27_zpsumvuvlus.jpg\" class=\"postimage\" alt=\"Image\"></a>\n<br> \n<a href=\"http://s1127.photobucket.com/user/justinwesty/media/Barry/image.jpg28_zpsxsmyygs6.jpg.html\" class=\"postlink\"><img src=\"http://i1127.photobucket.com/albums/l627/justinwesty/Barry/image.jpg28_zpsxsmyygs6.jpg\" class=\"postimage\" alt=\"Image\"></a>\n<br> This turned up and was promptly fitted, Im sure the purists out there that will be outraged but I want this bus to be drivable for the wife as well. Even for a 50+ year old bus the stearing was shocking in my defence!\n<br> \n<a href=\"http://s1127.photobucket.com/user/justinwesty/media/Barry/image.jpg20_zpsgoov2o7h.jpg.html\" class=\"postlink\"><img src=\"http://i1127.photobucket.com/albums/l627/justinwesty/Barry/image.jpg20_zpsgoov2o7h.jpg\" class=\"postimage\" alt=\"Image\"></a>\n<br> Driver side inner and outer sill and floor needed a fair bit of attention.\n<br> \n<a href=\"http://s1127.photobucket.com/user/justinwesty/media/Barry/image.jpg8_zpsolsyozpg.jpg.html\" class=\"postlink\"><img src=\"http://i1127.photobucket.com/albums/l627/justinwesty/Barry/image.jpg8_zpsolsyozpg.jpg\" class=\"postimage\" alt=\"Image\"></a>\n<br> \n<a href=\"http://s1127.photobucket.com/user/justinwesty/media/Barry/image.jpg5_zpst2xg5ul5.jpg.html\" class=\"postlink\"><img src=\"http://i1127.photobucket.com/albums/l627/justinwesty/Barry/image.jpg5_zpst2xg5ul5.jpg\" class=\"postimage\" alt=\"Image\"></a>\n<br> \n<a href=\"http://s1127.photobucket.com/user/justinwesty/media/Barry/image.jpg9_zps3fmzaqch.jpg.html\" class=\"postlink\"><img src=\"http://i1127.photobucket.com/albums/l627/justinwesty/Barry/image.jpg9_zps3fmzaqch.jpg\" class=\"postimage\" alt=\"Image\"></a>\n<br> \n<a href=\"http://s1127.photobucket.com/user/justinwesty/media/Barry/image.jpg12_zpsudcisms0.jpg.html\" class=\"postlink\"><img src=\"http://i1127.photobucket.com/albums/l627/justinwesty/Barry/image.jpg12_zpsudcisms0.jpg\" class=\"postimage\" alt=\"Image\"></a>\n<br> \n<a href=\"http://s1127.photobucket.com/user/justinwesty/media/Barry/image.jpg10_zps8v92sugt.jpg.html\" class=\"postlink\"><img src=\"http://i1127.photobucket.com/albums/l627/justinwesty/Barry/image.jpg10_zps8v92sugt.jpg\" class=\"postimage\" alt=\"Image\"></a>\n<br> \n<a href=\"http://s1127.photobucket.com/user/justinwesty/media/Barry/image.jpg11_zps64vacyhf.jpg.html\" class=\"postlink\"><img src=\"http://i1127.photobucket.com/albums/l627/justinwesty/Barry/image.jpg11_zps64vacyhf.jpg\" class=\"postimage\" alt=\"Image\"></a>\n<br> \n<br> So that where it up yo at the moment, next up drilling holes for deluxe trim, then engine out, fuel tank sorted (no readings on a perfectly working gauge) and then a respray!\n<br> \n<br> And then I 'accidentally' bought these when I popped into Retrodubs ......... Darn! \n<img class=\"smilies\" src=\"./images/smilies/icon_biggrin.gif\" width=\"15\" height=\"15\" alt=\":D\" title=\"Big Grin\"> \n<br> But they aren't going anywhere near the bus until paint is done!!!!!\n<br> \n<a href=\"http://s1127.photobucket.com/user/justinwesty/media/Barry/image.jpg2_zpsoqbomnt4.jpg.html\" class=\"postlink\"><img src=\"http://i1127.photobucket.com/albums/l627/justinwesty/Barry/image.jpg2_zpsoqbomnt4.jpg\" class=\"postimage\" alt=\"Image\"></a>\n<br> \n<br> I will keep updating this post as more work happens!\n<br> Cheers for now,\n<br> Justin",
